    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "49713e6c",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "49713e6c"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Typos in Expressions 2 - Logical Errors\n",
        "If you mis-type the singer’s name and run the cell, Colab does not report errors but the results in the output area is different from what we expected! In the example below, we expect an answer of 23, but we saw  \n",
        "\"Sorry, I don't have the information for  the input \"Camila Cabella\"    \n",
        "The result is not expected. We call these errors **logical errors** or **semantic errors**. Once this error happens we usually need to get back to our expression, carefully read through the expression, maybe using the results as hints. A seond idea is to click the *sparkle* icon to open the Colab AI to ask why you didn't get the expected number 23! One prompt to use is:  \n",
        "<tt>The result should be 23 but why \"sorry, ...\"? </tt>"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
